<br>
To my surprise, we were able to duo there with little effort or danger, eating up the 3 or 4 mobs that spawn there and pulling extras.<br>
<br>
The strategy was for me to become the mage's auxiliary pet.  Pet and I would engage mob, me with ToD.  Once the ToD procced and the mob was slowed, I'd back out and heal with Champion's BP while the pet tanked. The epic pet seems to generate a lot more aggro than lesser types.  If pet got low, I'd take over, build some aggro, and mage would DD the mob.  Mage had already summoned the bandages...<br>
<br>
We doinked there for about 30m and scored appreciable exp.<br>
<br>
Then we start accumulating LFG guildies and before long we were at CE without a healer.  We did FINE there except for one group of bastages that were pulling the castle... to BW!  Invariably,  some of the mobs would aggro on us when they ran by.  Sometimes we derailed, sometimes I paid for a rez...<br>
<br>
After 4 or 5 deaths in ToV that day, and 4 or so more in CE, I *still* had a postive exp day.<br>
